cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the challenge of learning with few samples, which is a major problem in machine learning. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to reduce the sample complexity of learning, which is a common research topic in this sub-category. 

The paper also deals with computer vision tasks, specifically scene classification and fine-grain bird classification, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper uses additional information provided per sample, such as semantic information about the relevance of features, which is a common research topic in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also proposes a new loss function, which is a common research topic in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

Finally, the paper develops an online algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deals with the development of algorithms inspired by the structure and function of the brain.
